    "possibleUpdate": false,
    "description": {
      "value": "<div>\n<p><strong>Absorbing Shield:</strong> This <em>+1 heavy steel shield</em> is flat black and seems to absorb light. Once every two days, on command, it can @Compendium[D35E.spells.dbzLkfBfQHCpcuao]{Disintegrate} an object that it touches, as the spell but requiring a melee touch attack.</p>\n<p>Strong transmutation; CL 17th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, <em>disintegrate</em>; Price 50,170 gp; Cost 25,170 gp + 2,000 XP.</p>\n</div>",
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">You strap a shield to your forearm and grip it with your hand. A heavy shield is so heavy that you can’t use your shield hand for anything else.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Wooden or Steel:</strong>&nbsp;Wooden and steel shields offer the same basic protection, though they respond differently to special attacks (such as warp wood and heat metal).</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Shield Bash Attacks:</strong>&nbsp;You can bash an opponent with a heavy shield, using it as an off-hand weapon. See Table 7–5: Weapons for the damage dealt by a shield bash. Used this way, a heavy shield is a martial bludgeoning weapon. For the purpose of penalties on attack rolls, treat a heavy shield as a one-handed weapon. If you use your shield as a weapon, you lose its AC bonus until your next action (usually until the next round). An enhancement bonus on a shield does not improve the effectiveness of a shield bash made with it, but the shield can be made into a magic weapon in its own right.</p>"
    },
